 House of Representatives Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila has urged Nigerians to create an enabling environment for persons loiving with disabilities. The Speaker spoke in Abuja while donating materials, including 20 wheel chairs and 10 scholarships to some people living with disabilities. The beneficiaries are: Saaka Aishat Adewunmi, Faiza Abubakar Jauro, Anna Samuel, Favour Ishaya, Emes Akaso Noel and five others. The occasion was the commemoration of the International Day of People With Disabilitie, which the House celebrated yesterday at the National Assembly. Gbajabiamila enjoined Nigerians to create a suitable environment for people living with disabilities to enable them achieve their dreams and aspirations. “On September 25, 2015, 193 countries of the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) adopted the UN 2030 Development Agenda, titled: Transforming Our World: The 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development. “The 17 broad goals of the 2030 Agenda are designed to remake our world, creating therefrom a better existence for all of mankind. “We have an unconscionable history of excluding persons with disabilities from participating in the conversation and processes of economic development and nation-building. “Government is an indispensable tool in the progressive mission to improve people’s lives, and it is our sacred responsibility to eliminate discriminatory laws and practices, replacing them with the infrastructure of opportunity that allows individuals to try, to succeed, to fail and to start all over again. “Amongst other things, the 2030 Agenda seeks to achieve a world free of inequality and the injustice that is its consequence. Of all the objectives set out in the agenda, there is none more urgent, more demanding of our commitment and effort, than that which requires us to jointly seek and achieve a drastic reduction in inequality here at home and across the world.”  